description: From Middle English heimon, equivalent to high +‎ man.

entries.meaning: A man of rank, especially a high rank; a superior.
examples: If not riding for life, that he is riding for immortality; and as the hero may perchance feel (for even a highman may feel like a hero), when he willingly throws away his existence in the hope of earning a glorious name,  […]

entries.meaning: (slang, obsolete) A loaded die that yields high numbers.
